Sentencas: Electron microscopy characterization across the cathode-electrolyte interface of two different types of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC) is performed to understand the origin of the cell performance disparity.
Titulo: Cathode-Electrolyte Interfaces with CGO Barrier Layers in SOFC

Sentencas: One IT-SOFC cell had a sprayed-cosintered Ce(0.90)Gd(0.01)O(1.95) (CGO10) barrier layer, the other had a barrier layer deposited by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) CGO10.
Titulo: Cathode-Electrolyte Interfaces with CGO Barrier Layers in SOFC

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy, transmission electron microscopy (TEM), and electron backscattered diffraction (EBSD) investigations conclude that the major source of the cell performance difference is attributed to CGO-YSZ interdiffusion in the sprayed-cosintered barrier layer.
Titulo: Cathode-Electrolyte Interfaces with CGO Barrier Layers in SOFC

Sentencas: From TEM and EBSD work, a dense CGO10 PLD layer is found to be deposited epitaxially on the 8YSZ electrolyte substrate-permitting a small amount of SrZrO(3) formation and minimizing CGO-YSZ interdiffusion.
Titulo: Cathode-Electrolyte Interfaces with CGO Barrier Layers in SOFC
